def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    """Returns priority with which we want to add item to each bin.

    Args:
        item: Size of item to be added to the bin.
        bins: Array of capacities for each bin.

    Return:
        Array of same size as bins with priority score of each bin.
    """
    ratios = item / bins
    priorities = np.zeros_like(bins)
    
    for i in range(len(bins)):
        if ratios[i] < 0.2:
            priorities[i] = 1 / (1 + np.exp(-ratios[i]))
        
        elif ratios[i] >= 0.2 and ratios[i] < 0.4:
            priorities[i] = np.power(ratios[i], 2)
        
        elif ratios[i] >= 0.4 and ratios[i] < 0.6:
            priorities[i] = np.log(ratios[i] + 1)
        
        elif ratios[i] >= 0.6 and ratios[i] < 0.8:
            priorities[i] = np.sin(ratios[i])
        
        else:
            priorities[i] = np.cosh(ratios[i] * np.pi) * np.tan(ratios[i]) + np.arctan(ratios[i])
    
    # Apply an additional transformation to priorities
    priorities = np.clip(priorities, 0, 1)  # Clip values between 0 and 1
    priorities = np.sort(priorities)[::-1]  # Sort priorities in descending order
    
    return priorities
